[+++ b/TESTING.asciidoc, +== Launching and debugging from an IDE, +== Debugging remotely from an IDE, +, +If you want to run Elasticsearch and be able to remotely attach the process, +for debugging purposes from your IDE, can start Elasticsearch using `ES_JAVA_OPTS`:, +, +---------------------------------------------------------------------------, +ES_JAVA_OPTS="-Xdebug -Xrunjdwp:server=y,transport=dt_socket,address=4000,suspend=y" ./bin/elasticsearch, +---------------------------------------------------------------------------, +, +Read your IDE documentation for how to attach a debugger to a JVM process., +]